revision.text:
The '''Bohemian National Alliance''' ({{lang-cz|Česko-Národní Sdružení}}) was an American political party founded in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], on September 6, 1914. The party represented [[Czech American]] voters who supported the creation of [[Czechoslovakia]] as a state independent of [[Austria-Hungary]]. The party was disestablished in 1918 after [[Czechoslovakia]] became an independent nation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.svu2000.org/cs-america/for-czechoslovakia/ |title=Czech America in the Struggle for Independent Czechoslovakia |publisher=[[Czechoslovak Society of Arts and Sciences]] |accessdate=2014-10-12}}</ref> The Bohemian National Alliance published a newspaper titled the Czechoslovak Review (originally the Bohemian Review) from 1916 until 1924.
==Bibliography== * Pergler, Charles. ''Bohemia's Claim To Independence (1916)'', Kessinger Publishing, LLC, 2010. * Masaryk, T.G. ''The voice of an oppressed people'', Library of Congress, 1917.
