A '''day school'''<ref>"Day school definition, a school open for instruction on weekdays only, usually from 9 a.m. until 3 p.m. {{cite web |url=http://www.dictionary.com/browse/day-school |title=Day school - dictionary.com}}</ref>—as opposed to a [[boarding school]]—is an educational [[institution]] where [[child]]ren<ref>"Founded in 1969. The Day School is one of the best preschools in the ... area." {{cite web |title=Preschool, Mothers Morning Out - The Day School |url=http://www.thedayschool-sscc.org}}</ref><ref>"It was graduation day for the Steppingstone Day School in Kew Gardens, Queens, and the 5-year-olds in their little white gowns and mortarboards ..." {{cite newspaper |newspaper=The New York Times |date=June 23, 1993 |author=Michael T. Kaufman |title=A Graduation Ceremony Earns Special Cheers |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/06/23/nyregion/about-new-york-a-graduation-ceremony-earns-special-cheers.html}}</ref> (or [[high school]] age [[adolescent]]s)<ref>"... for students in grades 3K-12. {{cite web |url=https://www.spartanburgdayschool.org |title= Day School: Independent Private School}}</ref> are given instruction during the day, after which the students return to their [[home]]s. The term can also be used to emphasize the length of full-day programs as opposed to [[After-school activity|after-school programs]], as in [[Jewish day school]].
The term '''one-day school''' may be used for a one-off series of lectures or classes, taking place on a single day, usually on a particular topic and usually directed at adult learners with little time to spare.<ref>"One-Day School. This 1-day, 4-hour school is designed to give players an overview of golf in a shortened time period." {{cite web |title=One-Day School - Chelsea Piers NYC |url=https://www.chelseapiers.com/golf/academy/schools-programs/one-day-school}}</ref>
